    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Considerations for Commerce Promotions\n Configure a Promotion\n Create a Promotion\n Create a Promotion Using a Template\n Create Promotions with Einstein\n Target Customers with a Promotion Segment\n Add a Promotion Tier\n Create a Coupon\n Define a Promotion Discount\n Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion\n Set Conditional Rules for a Promotion\n Localize Promotion Data\n Customize Promotions in Experience Builder\n Promotions in Checkout for B2B (Aura) Stores\n Example Promotions\n Prioritizing Promotions\n Remove a Promotion\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nDefine a Promotion Discount\n\nSet a target for your promotion discount, choose an adjustment type, and specify how much to deduct.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Promotions.\nSelect the promotion.\nOn the Discounts tab, click New.\nSelect a promotion tier.\nSee Add a Promotion Tier.\nSelect a target type.\nTo discount individual products, select Products.\nTo discount a subsection of products in a catalog, select Product Category. When you assign a promotion to a product category, it applies to all the variant products.\nTo discount the entire order, select Transaction and leave the Target field empty.\nTo discount all shipping methods on the order, select Shipping and leave the Target field empty. A shipping promotion is applied to all the shipping methods that the shopper is eligible for.\n(Optional) Select a target that matches the target type that you selected. If you left the Target field empty, select Transaction.\nA promotion can have multiple product targets as long as they have the same target type.\nSelect a currency ISO code.\nThis field is available only in multicurrency stores.\nSelect an adjustment type.\nFixed Amount Off Line Item Total—Deducts a monetary amount off a line item total.\nFixed Amount Off Transaction—Deducts a monetary amount off the entire order. This option is available only when you’re using the Transaction target type.\nFixed Amount Off Unit Price—Deducts a monetary amount off a single product item.\nFixed Price—Designates a promotional price for a product.\nPercentage Discount—Deducts a percent from the price of a product, transaction, or shipping.\nTotal Fixed Price—Designates a promotional price for a set of products.\nEnter the adjustment percent or monetary amount, depending on the type of adjustment that you selected.\nIf you enter a monetary amount and your account is multicurrency, choose a currency.\n(Optional) Enter a quantity limit to restrict the number of products that can receive the discount. The default is unlimited.\nSelect a target operator.\nNone—Neither of the other possible values apply. If the target type is for a transaction or shipping, select None.\nEqual to—The qualifying product or item in the qualifying category must be in the cart.\nNot Equal to—The qualifying product or item in the qualifying category isn’t required to be in the cart.\n(Optional) To require the customer to meet the limit to be eligible for the promotion, select Apply discount only when a cart reaches the quantity limit.\nClick Save.\nEXAMPLE To encourage your U.S. customers to start stocking up on healthy snacks, you want to provide a 10% discount on all energy bars in your store. When you create a promotion target:\nFor Target Type, select Product Category.\nFor Target, select Energy Bars.\nFor Currency ISO Code, select USD - U.S. Dollar.\nFor Adjustment Type, select Percentage Discount.\nFor Adjustment Percent, enter 10.\nSEE ALSO\nCommerce Promotions\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
